          <p><span id="docs-internal-guid-f7f5d5d1-7fff-a8bb-63d1-c97e1bdd56c5">
<p dir="ltr"><span>The Governor extended his stay at home and school closure order through April 24. We anticipate the school closure running at least through the end of April, and most likely longer. We will keep you updated as best we can. We will continue our distance learning plan and adjust as needed. Thank you for all of the work you are doing at home. All we expect is for you and the kids to try your best, stay safe, and keep a positive attitude. Please reach out to teachers if you are having trouble accessing classwork.  You can still sign up for our meal service by calling 406-646-7617.</span></p>
<div><span><br></span></div>
</span></p>

        
  
          
  
         
  
